### Basic suit

{% basicSuitImg /%}

On the top left and bottom right corners, there's a number overlapping an emoji (suit), it is the "Basic suit".

It is the most used game system of the deck, and thus, the most easy to use. When mapping new games, always give priority to it.

It contains 8 suits ({% suit id=0 /%}{% suit id=1 /%}{% suit id=2 /%}{% suit id=3 /%}{% suit id=4 /%}{% suit id=5 /%}{% suit id=6 /%}{% suit id=7 /%}) of 15 ranks (0...9 + XJQKA), named _15-ranked suits_, and 4 suits ({% suit id=8 /%}{% suit id=9 /%}{% suit id=10 /%}{% suit id=11 /%}) of 10 ranks (0...9), named _10-ranked suits_. They can be combined into several distributions.

#### Ranks

- 0...9: _Numeric ranks_ (0123456789).
  - 0 can be used as Joker or wildards.
  - 0 can be used as 10 in some games.
  - 1 can be used as an Ase.
- XJQKA: _Letter ranks_.
  - They are: 10, Jack, Queen, King, Ase.
  - Can be used as 10, 11, 12, 13, 14.

The other corners' numbers always end with this suit's number. Except when the rank is XJQKA, then the corners end with 01234 or 56789, respectivelly. For example, when the rank A, the other corners end in 1 or 6.

#### Suits

The suits can be classified into 2 categories by the amount of ranks they contain. So there are the 15-ranked suits ({% suit id=0 /%}{% suit id=1 /%}{% suit id=2 /%}{% suit id=3 /%}{% suit id=4 /%}{% suit id=5 /%}{% suit id=6 /%}{% suit id=7 /%}) or 10-ranked suits ({% suit id=8 /%}{% suit id=9 /%}{% suit id=10 /%}{% suit id=11 /%}).

{% suitsTable /%}

Each suit has a fixed [coin flip](#coin-flip) value. For example, {% suit id=0 /%} is always {% coinFlip id="no" /%}.

Each suit has a number id, it can be found on the _black part_ of the [Sequential number](#sequential-number).

#### 12 suits of 10 ranks

One combination is 12 suits ({% suit id=0 /%}{% suit id=1 /%}{% suit id=2 /%}{% suit id=3 /%}{% suit id=4 /%}{% suit id=5 /%}{% suit id=6 /%}{% suit id=7 /%}{% suit id=8 /%}{% suit id=9 /%}{% suit id=10 /%}{% suit id=11 /%}) of 10 rank (0...9).

There will be some unused cards, that may be optionally used to add extra ranks to some suits. The remaining cards are: the 5 _letter ranks_ (XJQKA) of the 15-ranked suits ({% suit id=0 /%}{% suit id=1 /%}{% suit id=2 /%}{% suit id=3 /%}{% suit id=4 /%}{% suit id=5 /%}{% suit id=6 /%}{% suit id=7 /%}).

To get it pick all the cards, and remove the _letter ranks_ (XJQKA).

Switch the suits for the ranks to have 10 suits (0...9) of 12 ranks ({% suit id=0 /%}{% suit id=1 /%}{% suit id=2 /%}{% suit id=3 /%}{% suit id=4 /%}{% suit id=5 /%}{% suit id=6 /%}{% suit id=7 /%}{% suit id=8 /%}{% suit id=9 /%}{% suit id=10 /%}{% suit id=11 /%}). Only use this if you need 9 or 10 suits of 11 or 12 ranks.

#### 8 suits of 15 ranks

Another combination is 8 suits ({% suit id=0 /%}{% suit id=1 /%}{% suit id=2 /%}{% suit id=3 /%}{% suit id=4 /%}{% suit id=5 /%}{% suit id=6 /%}{% suit id=7 /%}) of 15 ranks (0...9 + XJQKA).

There will be some unused cards, that may be optionally used to add extra suits. The remaining cards are: all the ranks (0...9) of the 10-ranked suits ({% suit id=8 /%}{% suit id=9 /%}{% suit id=10 /%}{% suit id=11 /%}).

To get it pick all the cards, and remove the 10-ranked suits ({% suit id=8 /%}{% suit id=9 /%}{% suit id=10 /%}{% suit id=11 /%}).

Switch the suits for the ranks to have 15 suits (0...9 + XJQKA) of 8 ranks ({% suit id=0 /%}{% suit id=1 /%}{% suit id=2 /%}{% suit id=3 /%}{% suit id=4 /%}{% suit id=5 /%}{% suit id=6 /%}{% suit id=7 /%}). Only use this if you need 13 to 15 suits of 8 or less ranks.

#### 10-level pyramidal deck with same ranks

You can also make an pyramidal deck of 10 levels, where each suit has the same rank. To do it, pick one 1, two 2's, three 3s... Up to ten 0's (0 would count as 10), no matter the suit you pick.

